”美国新冠肺炎确诊人数连日来迅速增加，并发生多起集聚性感染案例。
The number of people diagnosed with pneumonia in the US has risen rapidly over the past few days, with several cases of concentrated infection.
许多政府部门和企业相继进入抗疫模式，而包括美国大选在内的政界聚集活动也大幅减少。
Many government departments and businesses have moved into the epidemic mode, and political gatherings, including the US election, have declined dramatically.
截至发稿，据美国疾控中心（CDC）通报，截至当地时间10日晚，全美已有至少37个州和华盛顿特区出现新冠肺炎确诊病例至少975例，造成31人死亡，其中24例死亡病例出现在加州。
By the end of the night, at least 975 confirmed cases of new crown pneumonia in at least 37 states and Washington, D.C., had killed 31 people, 24 of them in California, the CDC reported.
另据《纽约时报》、NBC等多家媒体统计的全美实时数据，截至美东时间10日晚10点55分，全美确诊人数已达1004例。
The number of confirmed cases nationwide had reached 1,004 by 10: 55 p.m. EDT, according to real-time data from The New York Times, NBC and many other media outlets.
其中，美国密歇根州在10日晚确诊首例新冠肺炎病例，随后宣布进入紧急状态。
Michigan confirmed the first case of New Crown Pneumonia on the night of the declaration of a state of emergency.
有92人核酸检测推定阳性的马萨诸塞州早些时候也宣布了紧急状态。
Massachusetts, where 92 people tested positive for nucleic acid, also declared a state of emergency earlier this year.
目前，谷歌公司已建议所有在旧金山湾区和纽约办公室的员工，在工作内容许可的情况下改为在家办公。
Currently, Google has advised all employees in its offices in San Francisco Bay and New York to work from home if the job is available.
目前该公司共有11名在美国和加拿大的员工确诊。
The company now has 11 employees in the United States and Canada confirmed.
谷歌全球安全副主席拉考（Rackow）在回复美国有线电视新闻网（CNN）的邮件中证实了这一消息。
Backow, Google's vice president for global security, confirmed the news in an email to CNN.
此前谷歌已对在华盛顿州的员工发出同样建议。
Google had already made the same suggestion to employees in Washington state.
亚马逊9日也要求在美国湾区、西雅图地区、纽约、新泽西州以及意大利伦巴第大区的员工尽可能居家办公至月底。
Amazon 9 also called for the United States Gulf, Seattle, New York, New Jersey and Italy's Lombardy region employees as far as possible from home until the end of the month.
原定于4月14日在旧金山的莫斯克尼中心南区举行的亚马逊云计算大会已确定取消。
The Amazon Cloud Computing Conference, originally scheduled to take place on 14 April in the southern part of the Moskeney centre in San Francisco, has been definitively cancelled.
这是亚马逊云计算部门在全国和全世界举办的系列城市峰会之一。
This is one of the series of city summits organized by Amazon Cloud Computing in the country and around the world.
去年，旧金山的云计算大会吸引了6000多名与会者。
Last year, San Francisco's Cloud Computing Congress attracted more than 6,000 participants.
目前有一名在西雅图的亚马逊员工确诊感染新冠肺炎。
A Seattle-based Amazon employee has been diagnosed with pneumonia.
上个月亚马逊已经禁止员工在美国国内进行不必要的旅行。
Amazon last month banned employees from making unnecessary trips inside the U. S.
在5日有两名员工确诊的微软也要求全体员工在家工作至3月25日。
Microsoft, which had two staff members on the 5th, also required all employees to work from home until March 25.
脸书、推特等科技巨头都出台了类似政策。
Facebook, Twitter and other tech giants have similar policies.
除了科技巨头，在教育界，一些大中小学开始采取停课措施，人群聚集的活动纷纷取消。
In addition to the technology giants, in the education sector, some schools and universities began to take measures to suspend classes, crowd-gathering activities have been cancelled.
据加州大学官方网站的消息，加州大学各分校已经陆续取消面对面授课，改为开展线上课程。
UC campuses have moved from face-to-face classes to online courses, according to the University of California website.
其中加州大学洛杉矶分校（UCLA）将线下课程暂停至4月10日春季学期第二周结束，期末考试也将远程进行，所有超过100人的非必要集会全部取消。
The University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA) suspended offline classes until the end of the second week of spring on April 10, and final exams will be conducted remotely, cancelling all non-essential gatherings of more than 100 people.
加州大学河滨分校则停止线下课程至4月3日，圣巴巴拉分校至4月底。
The University of California, Riverside, suspended offline classes until April 3 at Santa Barbara.
纽约州州长科莫10日宣布，在该州疫情最严重的新罗谢尔（New Rochelle）地区划定一个半径1.6公里的控制区，区内所有学校及设施将从3月12日到25日全面关闭，国民警卫队将进行协助上门递送食品并清洁公共区域。
New York Governor Sebastian Komo announced Monday that the state's worst affected area, New Rochelle, will have a 1.6-kilometer radius. All schools and facilities in the area will be closed from March 12 to 25, and the National Guard will assist with door-to-door food deliveries and clean up public areas.
目前该计划将持续到3月25日。
The plan now runs until 25 March.
联合国也宣布从10日晚8点起，暂时停止对公众开放位于纽约的总部大楼。
The United Nations also announced the temporary closure of the Headquarters building in New York from 8 p.m. on the tenth.
重新开放时间待定。
Reopening time to be determined.
目前纽约暂无联合国工作人员被确诊。
No United Nations staff member is currently diagnosed in New York.
原定于4月在加州举行的科切拉（Coachella）和驿马乡村音乐节（Stagecoach）都已被推迟至10月举行。
Both Coachella and Stagecoach, originally scheduled for April in California, have been postponed to October.
美国政坛也受疫情影响放慢了脚步。
American politics have also been slowed by the epidemic.
据《国会山报》报道，民主党参议员桑德斯以及前副总统拜登都取消了原定于10日晚间在俄亥俄州举行的竞选集会。
Democratic Senator Sanders and former Vice President Joe Biden canceled an election rally scheduled for October night in Ohio, the Capitol Hill newspaper reported.
副总统彭斯则在10日表示，特朗普竞选团队根据每天的情况研判是否继续举行竞选集会，他还暗示自己与特朗普不会停止握手。
Vice President Burns said on the 10th that the Trump campaign was trying to decide whether to proceed with the rally on a daily basis, and hinted that he and Trump would not stop shaking hands.
据CNN此前援引特朗普竞选团队成员消息，特朗普可能在10日晚宣布下一次集会活动，但目前还没有任何相关消息。
Trump could announce his next rally on the night of the 10th, according to CNN, citing members of the Trump campaign team, but there has been no news so far.
此外，还有多名美国国会议员相继宣布进行“自我隔离”。
In addition, several members of the United States Congress have declared "self-segregation."
当地时间10日，弗吉尼亚州民主党众议员拜尔（Don Beyer）在得知10天前与自己共进晚餐的一位友人新冠病毒检测呈阳性后，宣布进行“自我隔离”至下周一（16日）。
Virginia Democrat Don Beyer announced Monday that he was "self-isolated" after learning that a friend he had dined with 10 days earlier had tested positive for the virus.
本周拜尔曾前往国会山开会，但他和一同就餐的妻子均未出现症状。
Bair visited Capitol Hill for a meeting this week, but neither he nor his wife, who eats with him, showed any symptoms.
据美国商业内幕网站统计，拜尔至少是第六位与新冠病毒感染者接触后宣布隔离的国会议员。
Bayer is at least the sixth member of Congress to be declared isolated after coming into contact with people infected with the virus, according to US business insider sites.
但在被问及国会大厦是否应因新冠病毒威胁而暂时关闭时，美国众议院议长佩洛西表示，目前没有理由这样做。
But when asked whether the Capitol building should be temporarily closed because of the new crown virus, House Speaker Nancy Pelosi said there was no reason to do so at the moment.
